article.headline: Boise St. 93, Idaho St. 61
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Boise State got 24 points, including six 3-pointers, from Tyler Tiedeman and beat Idaho State 93-61 on Wednesday night. The Western Athletic Conference Broncos (6-2) built a 20-point lead over the Big Sky Conference Bengals (2-6) with about eight minutes left in the first half and never led by less than 20 the rest of the game. Tiedeman hit six of nine 3-point attempts and eight of 11 shots from the field. Reggie Larry scored 19 points and Matt Nelson had 13 points, eight rebounds and six assists for Boise State. Idaho State got 23 points from Matt Stucki and 12 points and six rebounds from Logan Kinghorn.
